The paper deals with the problem of detecting malware-generated domains, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of machine learning and neural networks to detect these domains suggests that the paper could also be classified under artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves the development of a data-driven approach to detect malware, which could also be classified under software engineering (cs.SE).
